4 This place is just what the Aliante Station needs.  Great food and generous portions at a fair price.   The table and seat were dirty and sticky when we arrived but this wasn't discovered until after the stickiness was transferred to our arms and clothing.  The waitress was apologetic and she did her best to clean the table but really it whoever bussed the table should have noticed and taken care of it before we were seated.   The escargot appetizer was one of the best I have ever had.  Just the right amount of garlic and mushrooms. The chewy lightly toasted bread was a nice touch.    Fish and chips were made fresh with just the right amount of batter and cooked to perfection.  Apparently the tarter sauce is made fresh also as witnessed by the fact it arrived about 10 minutes after the dish was placed on the table.  The "chips" were a meal and prepared in a way that is hard to describe but incredibly delicious.  The osso bucco was decent.  A  generous portion but a little gristly. The flavor was very good but the texture was "different'. The dish was accompanied by mushroom risotto.  I am not a huge fan of risotto and this rendition  didn't change my feelings. The flavor was nice but the mushrooms were a bit chewy.  The marscapone cheesecake was incredibly light and full of flavor.  Despite the fact that we were stuffed, we devoured every morsel of this delightful dessert.   Overall it was great meal and I intend to be a frequent customer.
5 This was my first time trying their breakfast and just the same as their lunch/dinner, I loved everything!  I still can't get over the quality of food at such great prices. We had lox and bagel and it was just outstanding. The lox was good and plentiful but the best part about it was it came with heirloom tomatoes! You shoulda seen how big my eyes got when the server put down the plate. Oh, that yellow tomato tasted as good as it looked. It was so fresh, sweet and delicious--what a pleasant surprise to have heirloom tomatoes with my breakfast! The quiche Lorraine was really good with a perfect, flakey crust. It came with a side of field greens in a simple citrusy dressing.  I can't say enough good things about this place. It's the best thing that's happened to NLV. I hope they continue to be able to put out high quality food at these incredible prices for long as they possibly can. I will be back. A lot.
